On 2002-11-24 at 19:04 +0100, Eric Smith wrote:
> I use aliases of the following form:
> 
> alias -g M='|more'
> 
> Is it possible to force a carriage return after the `more' so that I may just
> press (say) `M' and the command will execute?

bindkey -s M '|more\n'

